{
  "answer": "**The verse you're referring to appears in \"The Wanderer,\" chapter 11 of *Old English Elegies*.**[^1]\n\nThe key line, spoken by the wanderer reflecting on his lost lord (\"gold-friend\"), reads: \"since long ago my gold-friend / the earth's darkness covered.\" This occurs early in the poem, as the speaker describes being \"stripped of my homeland\" after his patron's death and burial.[^1]\n\n[^1]: *Old English Elegies*, \"The Wanderer\" [paragraph](/works/unknown-old-english-elegies-d5fe9e/11-the-wanderer/translation/#p-9462cc).",
